# ~/claude-discord/<instance>/.bot.env — per-instance overrides for the
# claude-discord@.service systemd unit. install.sh <instance> seeds this
# file from this template.
#
# Systemd reads the file as plain KEY=VALUE pairs. No shell expansion,
# no quoting tricks — write literal paths.
#
# This repo ships opinionated defaults: the vox-plugins discord + scheduler
# plugins are loaded and the model is pinned to claude-opus-4-7[1m] (the
# 1M-context variant) at max effort. If that's not what you want, comment
# these lines back out or point them at different values.

# --- PLUGINS (opinionated) ----------------------------------------------

# Space-separated plugin specs for --dangerously-load-development-channels.
# install.sh also formally installs these via `claude plugin install`.
# Add `plugin:slack@vox-plugins` for the Slack channel too (set its tokens +
# SLACK_OWNER_ID below, the same way discord uses DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN/OWNER_ID).
BOT_PLUGINS=plugin:discord@vox-plugins plugin:scheduler@vox-plugins

# --- CHANNEL TOKENS + OWNER ---------------------------------------------

# Tokens + owner id for each channel in BOT_PLUGINS. Only the owner can run the
# /access slash command that authorizes channels and DM users. (These can instead
# live in each channel's state-dir .env, but .bot.env is simplest.) Uncomment what you use.

# Discord:
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=MTIz...
# DISCORD_OWNER_ID=000000000000000000          # your Discord user snowflake

# Slack (Socket Mode — needs both tokens):
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...
# SLACK_OWNER_ID=U0000000                       # your Slack member id (U…)

# --- MODEL SELECTION (opinionated) --------------------------------------

ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7[1m]
CLAUDE_CODE_SUBAGENT_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7[1m]
CLAUDE_CODE_EFFORT_LEVEL=max

# --- PER-INSTANCE DEFAULTS (uncomment to override) ----------------------

# The `claude --resume <name>` session this bot resumes. Defaults to the
# instance name (e.g. `claude-discord@tinyclaw` resumes the `tinyclaw`
# session). Must already exist (create it with `claude -n <name>` first).
# BOT_SESSION_NAME=my-custom-session

# Screen session name the wrapper runs `claude` inside. Defaults to
# `claude-discord-<instance>` (already unique per instance). Override
# only if you really want a specific name.
# SCREEN_SESSION=my-custom-screen

# --- MESSAGE LOGGING (opt-in; discord plugin >= 0.2.30, slack >= 0.1.14) -

# Point the discord/slack channel plugins at a JSONL file and they append
# every message — inbound (including while dunked) plus the bot's own replies
# (tagged "out":true) — one record per line {chat_id, message_id, user,
# user_id, ts, body}. Only AUTHORIZED channels are logged; unauthorized ones
# are skipped. Unset = no logging (the default). Use ABSOLUTE paths (systemd
# does no shell expansion); one file per surface, same folder. Replace
# <user>/<instance> with this bot's actual path.
# DISCORD_MESSAGE_LOG=/home/<user>/claude-discord/<instance>/notes/chatlogs/discord.jsonl
# SLACK_MESSAGE_LOG=/home/<user>/claude-discord/<instance>/notes/chatlogs/slack.jsonl
